 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Design-In Technology Strategist- Education and Workstation Microsoft 7,267 reviews United States Full-time Microsoft 7,267 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. The Device Partner Sales team, who build and sell Intelligent Edge Device and Intelligent Cloud solutions together with our partners, plays a critical role in achieving this mission. We’re positioned right at the intersection of customers, original equipment manufacturers and channel partners. We work closely with internal engineering, marketing, business group, and our external device partner ecosystem to deliver fantastic customer experiences powered by Microsoft platforms – Windows, Microsoft 365, along with Azure IoT and Azure Stack. 
Opportunities in DPS are expansive because we span the entire product lifecycle - from incubation, prototyping and portfolio planning to the design-in, sell-in and sell-out motions that touch consumer and business customers. We’re also driving innovative IoT solutions & AI services partnering with IoT team and helping companies with their digital transformations. All of this wraps up under our unique charter of working with partners to build and sell Intelligent Edge devices and solutions that empower everyone to achieve more. As a member of our team, you’ll be part of growing a multi-billion-dollar business and charting new areas of innovation. If that appeals to you, it’s an exciting time to be here in DPS. 
Responsibilities 
Drive Microsoft platform & technology adoption with partners: 
This role will own the technical design-in strategy and execution for our Education and Workstation device portfolios with a strategic Microsoft Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM). 
This position will find new opportunities for innovative devices and aligning our strategic OEM to technologies to support the market acceptance of these devices. 
You will closely collaborate with internal stakeholders (for instance our strategic OEM account leader, Windows marketing and engineering teams) to best leverage our resources and make a bigger impact with aligned priority across our modern workplace solutions including Office, Teams, etc. 
Act as a trusted advisor to inform partners on key device OS platform investments to enable technology adoption and deliver results through identification and execution of technical or business best practices or requirements 
Leverage excellent technical sales skills to drive essential technology design wins, driving both short- and long-term opportunities to deliver world-class devices and solutions powered by Microsoft 
Represent partner as an internal advocate from technical or business needs/concerns and as technical liaison to internal sales, product, marketing, or channel organizations 
Keep up to date with trends and competitive insights and engage partners and internal teams to enhance our industry-leading solutions/services further 
Deliver excellent cross-group collaboration work and teamwork across the Global Technical Sales teams coordinated with the applicable account teams 
Infuse Microsoft AI (voice, vision, search, and language) and machine learning capability to build industry leading devices and solutions. 
Qualifications 
Experiences Required: Education, Key Experiences, Skills and Knowledge: 
The ideal candidate should: 
Possess a combination of technical acumen, business insight and influence skills to lead design-in, portfolio management and technical engagements 
Have deep experience in device and cloud solutions 
Fuse the talents of Hardware and Software product planning, device sales and cross-functional leadership to drive our technical and early business development efforts 
Be able to work deeply with partners, great interpersonal and communications skills; ability to define a vision, set goals, objectives and work across virtual teams and across Microsoft organizations to achieve specific, well-defined outcomes 
Understand product features and benefits from technical requirements perspective while balancing business benefits and trade-offs 
Have excellent verbal and written communication ability with requisite interpersonal skills to partner, collaborate and build relationships with partner accounts, account/segment marketing teams and Microsoft product/marketing groups.
 Demonstrate the ability to anticipate risk/opportunity, then identifies and evangelizes opportunities and priorities for future action - while being able to focus on achieving concrete results individually or through partner execution 
Understand how to get things done and have organizational agility to overcome obstacles and achieve objectives with a variety of stakeholders 
Creatively develop original ideas, approaches and solutions to typical, unusual or difficult situations or problems 
Be customer-focused, responsive and action-oriented to meet customer needs while maintaining a positive, professional image of Microsoft 
Passion for technology and Microsoft products. 
This position requires domestic and international travel. 
Minimum Qualifications: 
4+ years’ experience with relevant technologies (e.g., devices, Microsoft platform or hardware development) 
Preferred Qualifications: 
Bachelor's Degree in Information Technology, Engineering, Business, Computer Science, or related field AND 5+ years of technical consulting, technical consultative selling, practice building, or related technical/sales experience 
Master's Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business or related field AND 3+ years of technical consulting, technical consultative selling, practice building, or related technical/sales experience OR equivalent experience 
Formal education or experience in Business or Sales 
Fluency in a second language other than English 
Personal Attributes and Competencies: 
Proven ability to work independently and effectively with limited supervision 
A strong sense of teamwork, with ability to both build and work with virtual teams in cross-group collaborative scenarios 
Capable of effectively navigating complex business challenges in ambiguous settings with solid business judgment and risk management 
Strong interpersonal skills with executive credibility 
Lifelong learner with a growth mindset that continually raises the bar on personal impact and performance 
Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. If you need assistance and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application or the recruiting process, please send a request via the Accommodation request form. 
